A book penned by Shakthi TV Journalist Uma Chandraprakash was unveiled at the auditorium of the Capital Maharaja Organisation Limited on the evening of Wednesday, April 30.
The book which is published by the Veerakesari Institution includes articles on History, Archaeology, Arts, Biology and Culture was titled Pettagam.
The event was held under the auspices of the Chief Lecturer of the Koppai Teaching School, S. Laleeyath included Professor Vasantha Arasaratnam Vice Chancellor from the University of Jaffna who participated as the Chief Guest and Senior Journalist and Writer, Aneena Lashmi Rasathurai appeared as the Guest of Honour at the event.
The first copy of the boo Pettagam was presented to the Chairman of the Sri Lanka Women’s Union Neela Dayabaran.

