Former President Mahinda Rajapaksa noted at a meeting held at the Abhayarama Viharaya in Narahenpita on Wednesday that certain positive features can be seen in the 19th Amendment to the constitution.
He went on to state that the fact that the President is responsible to parliament is a pleasant sign as well as. He further added that the Public Service Commission as well as the Bribery Commission is independent and those responsible for the independence of these institution now hold them responsible to the parliament.



