The 82nd commemoration of the late Anagarika Dharmapala was presided by President Maithripala Sirisena on the morning of Wednesday April 29.
The commemoration event which was attended by the Head of State took place at the Mahabodhi Agrashawaka Maha Viharaya in Maradana.
The president paid floral tributes to the statue of the late Anagarika Dharmapala located at the premises of the Mahabodhi Agrashawaka Maha Viharaya.
Subsequently, the President paid homage to the Sacred Relics of Sariputta and Moggallana arahath theros placed at the Mahabodhi Agrashawaka Maha Viharaya.


