Visiting Bhutan Prime Minister Shering Tobgay, who is on a three-day state visit to the country, called on President Maithripala Sirisena on Friday.
The duo held bilateral discussion at the Presidential Secretariat on Friday morning. The two leaders signed a number of MOUs, subsequent to the discussions.
The Bhutan Prime Minister arrived in the country on Thursday on a three-day visit to the country. The Ministry of External Affairs noted that the visiting Bhutan Prime Minister is slated to hold talks with the prime minister and other political leaders.

