A total of 29 people have been admitted to the Weligama District Hospital after having sustained injuries in altercations or accidents.
Our correspondent noted that as of  6 a.m. Tuesday  morning to 6 a.m. Wednesday morning – April 14 to April 15 morning – a total of 29 patients were admitted.
Assistant Medical Officer of the Weligama District Hospital Dr. Bandularathna noted that 29 patients have been admitted to the hospital. Many patients have been admitted owing to accidents, altercations, but it was observed that the main reason behind these accidents was the use of narcotics.

