Minister Vijith Wijayamuni Zoysa, addressing a public meeting in Bibila on Friday said that certain groups, with no political patience, have begun to ask questions.
He went on to add that there are a few, who should be accountable for the party’s loss at the presidential election, but the main person is Wimal Weerawansa.
He went on further to add that Wimal Weerawansas’ and Udaya Gammanpilas’ will have to go around the village if the electorate election system is introduced. He also added that they have mentioned, in worry,  that such a system would lead to a hundred beatings within the hundred days and that few of member of the party with better judgement had made President Maithripala Sirisena the President of the Party.

